properties.query:
SELECT
  a.zipcode,
  a.name,
  a.city,
  a.state,
  a.area_name
FROM
  FLOWFILE a
INNER JOIN (
  SELECT
    zipcode,
    MIN(row_index) AS min_index
  FROM
    FLOWFILE
  GROUP BY
    zipcode
) b
ON
  a.zipcode = b.zipcode
  AND a.row_index = b.min_index
ORDER BY a.zipcode

SELECT "CPT Code" AS cpt_id, 
	   "Level of Severity" AS severity, 
	   "Time Spent" AS time_spent
FROM FLOWFILE

processors.name: Initialize Flow
processors.comments:
This NiFi processor initiates the entire process to retrieve information from various APIs. It sets up the parameters that will be used in other process groups. 

*** currentIndex:  This index helps in retrieving data from APIs that contain too many records to fetch in a single request. Initially, the index is set to 0, and subsequent processors increment this index to retrieve the next batch of records.
*** increaseIndex:  The increment to find the next 1000 records from the API will be 1000.
*** limit:  This number specifies the amount of records that the API's GET request will retrieve.

properties.query:
SELECT 
    ROW_NUMBER() OVER (ORDER BY "DELIVERY ZIPCODE") AS row_index, 
    "DELIVERY ZIPCODE" AS zipcode,
	"LOCALE NAME" AS name, 
	"PHYSICAL CITY" AS city,
	"PHYSICAL STATE" AS state, 
	"AREA NAME" AS area_name 
FROM 
    FLOWFILE
